  "response": "Here are some tips to prepare for NEET 2017:\n\n1. Understand the Syllabus\n- CBSE/NCERT syllabus for Physics, Chemistry, and Biology\n- Thoroughly review Class 11 and 12 topics\n\n2. Study Material\n- NCERT textbooks (primary source)\n- Reference books like HC Verma, RC Mukerjee\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Mock test series\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Study Plan\n- Create a structured daily study schedule\n- Allocate time for each subject\n- Focus on weak areas\n- Regular revision\n- Practice mock tests\n\n4. Subject-wise Preparation\nPhysics:\n- Concentrate on numerical problems\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Focus on mechanics, electricity, optics\n\nChemistry:\n- Learn periodic table\n- Practice chemical equations\n- Focus on organic and inorganic chemistry\n\nBiology:\n- Focus on diagrams\n- Learn classification\n- Study human physiology in detail\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Time management\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Stay physically and mentally healthy\n- Practice meditation/yoga\n- Get sufficient sleep\n\n6. Important Books\n- NCERT textbooks\n- Objective NCERT at your fingertips\n- MTG NEET guides",
